ZH: 天下是我们共同的家园。
EN: The world is our common home.

ZH: 天下大势，分久必合，合久必分。
EN: The general trend of the world is that things that have been separated for a long time will unite, and things that have been united for a long time will separate.

ZH: 天下无不散之宴席。
EN: All feasts must come to an end.

ZH: 天下没有不散的宴席。
EN: There is no feast that will not end.

ZH: 天下熙熙，皆为利来；天下攘攘，皆为利往。
EN: The hustle and bustle in the world stems from seeking profit.

ZH: 天下为公。
EN: The world belongs to everyone.

ZH: 天下事有难易，空言语忍耐。
EN: In all under heaven there are situations difficult to oppose, and that is when discretion is the better part of valor.

ZH: 天下没有不散的筵席。
EN: There is no everlasting feast under heaven.

ZH: 天下不是公道，自己要学着把握命运。
EN: The world is not fair; one must learn to control one's own destiny.

ZH: 天下定义丧心病狂的人。
EN: The world condemns heartless and crazy people.

ZH: 天下一家。
EN: The world is one family.

ZH: 天下事，难易皆为人情。
EN: In the world, all matters are governed by human feelings.

ZH: 天下乌鸦一般黑。
EN: The whole world is as black as a crow.

ZH: 天下事应乖，莫道公道无。
EN: The ways of the world can be straightforward or perverse but don't deny the existence of justice.

ZH: 天下之事如长风。
EN: The affairs of the world are as transient as the wind.

ZH: 天下普遍繁荣。
EN: General prosperity prevails under heaven.

ZH: 天下为社稷。
EN: The world is the foundation of a country.

ZH: 天下剧变。
EN: A great upheaval under heaven.

ZH: 天下状世间生善恶毕竟自在一点上所展转。
EN: In the world, all things are naturally brought to good or evil finally do revolve around a single point.

ZH: 天下疯癫。
EN: The whole world has gone mad.
